  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "O love, how deep, how broad, how high, How passing thought and fantasy, That God, the Son of God, should take Our mortal form for mortals&#39; sake!",
    "v2": "He sent no angel to our race Of higher or of lower place, But wore the robe of human frame And He Himself, to this world came.",
    "v3": "Nor willed He only to appear; His pleasure was to tarry here; And God and Man with man would be The space of thirty years and three.",
    "v4": "For us baptized, for us He bore His holy fast and hungered sore, For us temptations sharp He knew; For us the tempter overthrew.",
    "v5": "For us He prayed; for us He taught; For us His daily works He wrought; By words and signs and actions thus Still seeking not Himself, but us."
  },
